    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of rapid-growing shade tree, native to eastern North America and widely cultivated elsewhere. It grows to 18 m (60 feet) in height. Its wood is soft, but used for crating and inexpensive furniture. It can produce syrup, but is low yield. It drops branches and produces numerous shoots, making it problematic as an ornamental, although several useful varieties have been produced.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000027681/Brady and Clauser, Materials Handbook (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Snel groeiende schaduwboom die inheems is in het oosten van Noord-Amerika en elders op grote schaal wordt gekweekt. De boom kan 18 meter hoog worden. Het hout is zacht, maar wordt wel gebruikt voor kisten en goedkope meubels. De boom produceert siroop, maar in kleine hoeveelheden. De takken vallen af en er ontstaan een groot aantal spruiten, waardoor het een lastige sierboom is, hoewel er diverse bruikbare variëteiten zijn gekweekt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>原生於北美洲東部的喬木種名，生長速度快，高度可達18公尺（60英尺），可供遮蔭，各地皆廣為栽植。其木材質軟，但可做為板條箱及平價家具的材料。其汁液可製成糖漿，但產量不豐。由於銀楓的樹枝易落，且多生嫩枝，雖已培育出數種實用性高的品種，仍不適合做為觀賞植物。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
